    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Consul General at Peiping (
                        Clubb
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1948v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d772</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">772</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1948-10-28T04:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1948-10-28T04:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-10-28T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-10-28T04:00:00-05:00" n="772" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d772">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/10–2848: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-10-28T17:00:00+08:00">October 28, 1948—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 28—8:14 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>403. ReDeptel 1484, October 23 and Tientsin 309.<note n="27" xml:id="d772fn27">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> According Embtel 196, October 26,<note n="28" xml:id="d772fn28">Sent to the Department as telegram No. 1994, <ref target="#pg_861">p. 861</ref>.</note> this office’s warning follows text
                    Deptel 469 [<hi rend="italic">1469</hi>].<note n="29" xml:id="d772fn29">October
                        19, 6 p.m., <ref target="#pg_853">p. 853</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>It is proposed, unless contrary instructions are received, to notify concerned
                    Americans by same communication that efforts are being made in absence adequate
                    shipping facilities to arrange for sea transport from Tientsin between November
                    15 and December 1 and asking concerned Americans indicate whether they desire
                    take advantage those facilities; this, of course, assuming such non-emergency
                    warning will be issued by first indicated date.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 403; repeated Nanking 599, Shanghai 413 and Tientsin.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clubb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
